wiki.summary: “JUMPIN” is the 18th track on Playboi Carti’s 3rd studio album, MUSIC Carti and Uzi talk about the typical rapper lifestyle which involves money, drugs and guns. they mention several drugs like Oxy, Molly, and Perc-10, all with luxury, expensive cars, and jewelry. The song was produced by the legendary and famous producer D. Hill, who sadly passed away on October 14, 2021. Carti would mention this via Instagram stories, where, quoting a story from Veeze, he said; “WE DOING IT 4 DHILL”. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “JUMPIN” is the 18th track on Playboi Carti’s 3rd studio album, MUSIC Carti and Uzi talk about the typical rapper lifestyle which involves money, drugs and guns. they mention several drugs like Oxy, Molly, and Perc-10, all with luxury, expensive cars, and jewelry. The song was produced by the legendary and famous producer D. Hill, who sadly passed away on October 14, 2021. Carti would mention this via Instagram stories, where, quoting a story from Veeze, he said; “WE DOING IT 4 DHILL”. While the collaboration with Lil Uzi Vert was rumored, Playboi Carti would confirm it even hours before the album or tracklist release by messaging Kai Cenat on Instagram about the album’s delay, including a personal message that said “YO BOY UZI SNAPPED” due to the friendship between Kai Cenat and Lil Uzi Vert. Hours before the album dropped, there were rumors about an interlude and a track with Lil Uzi Vert being on it, with some people also claiming that the song (later “JUMPIN”), is from the Pink Tape era. (This hasn’t been fully confirmed yet, but it would explain why there are so many references to his album and Carti’s old album name “Narcissist” in the song) Read more on Last.fm.
